This is a long time in coming, and something I resurrected from the depths of my sandbox. The original idea of a phone call from a berating mother came from Nexescore. The original concept didn't work, but I saw potential and asked to revamp it. I did, but I was ultimately unsatisfied. I waited and a whole year later, I figured out how I want the story to finish.

Yes, I'm going way old-school with my interpretation of D-class, but I don't care.

Thanks to GibberingEloquence for the modern review.

First photo is mine, second from Wikipedia and is public domain.





